column5: Looks like I missed out on a fantastic trip....bummer....  Now that is a big bleepin Laker, especially through the ice!  Good shootin guys.   Cheers, Ron...
WOW! Great fish!  Got tired of catching all those giant 'eyes on Quinte, and had to move to something new eh Lloyd?  Video wasn't put together half bad either
yes you did...........
AS MUCH AS I LIKE BIG EYES ,I LIKE BIG LAKERS THROUGH THE ICE EVEN BETTER. THEY FIGHT SO MUCH BETTER THEN EYES AND BITE ALL DAY LONG TOO
I don't have any more pictures everyone gave me their cameras to take the pictures of fish and I took videos
Okay.. Dano and Lloyd it is! lol
nice trip guys awesome video terry
Awesome trip, thats one big laker through the ice  Headed up this week can only hope the fishn half that good to us.
Tank !
Nice ice fishing trip! That big laker must be 25-30 lbs Great video, thanks for posting it.

The laker calculator puts it between 41 and 43 lbs... here's a similar fish that was kept and weighed in at 43 lbs. I think Lloyd's fish was slightly longer than this one. None of us really care what it weighs... it will be hard to beat in years to come for sure.. but gives us a goal ! lol
here are some videos of the guys fishing at the 3 minute mark it gets exciting  when you hear me saying bleep..it's to hide the more colorful words
I'll call that and raise ya another BLEEPEDY BLEEP!!  Sweeeeeet!!
WOW    27 min. fight     Incredible
Hey Wayne, I think your property value just went up 20%
That is awesome.  What a tank.
Way ta go Lloyd! That's a troutasauris! Congrats! HH
After measuring my boots... that fish was 47 to 48 inches long... Laker calculator estimates it at 43 lbs !!!
beautiful fish. temagami was slow for us, a few lakers but no monsters.  i'm so glad to see you released it for another day. cheers
WWOOOOOOOOWWWWWWWWW
Wayne should we tell them where we caught it  I mean which lake  Lloyd caught it on or wait and he can offer a guide service for monsters the lucky bleep
Well done guys, congrat's Lloyd....
Wow, what a monster.  Congrats Lloyd  Joey
I wanna catch one of those NICE FISH!  Thx Terry
Nice tank !! Congrats
Lloyd... Guide.. what...who do you think took him there in the first place!  As for which lake.. and where... I'll just say it's accessible to anyone that wants to do some travelling.....
That's a donkey! Great job on the release
Awesome man, outstanding catch. Get that fish replicated!
I am NOT worthy!!!!!! Awesome!
AWESOME!!!!!!!!!  I'm in awe right now big time....Way to go boys!!!!
THANKS TERRY FOR THE GREAT VID!!!! SEE YOU ON SAT ON SIMCOE
you bet, see you Saturday
